    <property>
      <content>The PhenoTips development team is happy to announce the availability of the ninth milestone of PhenoTips 1.0, a release full of new features aiding collaboration. The highlights of the release are:&#xd;
&#xd;
* An improved interface for creating **user groups**, which can be used to delimit users by various criteria, such as //institution//, //specialty//, //role//, or //access level//.&#xd;
* Users can specify a **patient record visibility**, defining if a record is visible or not to other users.&#xd;
* Special rights on a patient record can be granted for other users or groups (**collaborators**).&#xd;
* The creator of a patient record is considered the **owner of the record**, but now the ownership can be **transfered** to another user or group.&#xd;
* A new and easy to use **form customization wizard** can be used by administrators to change which sections and fields are displayed in the patient record. This configuration can be defined globally, but also for each user group.&#xd;
* **Improved navigation**: **breadcrumbs** allow quickly going upwards in the hierarchy, a **quick patient search** box allows searching for patients based on their identifier or their name, and a **quick patient creation** button is always available in the header.&#xd;
* Measurements can now be entered in **imperial units**, if activated from the configuration.&#xd;
&#xd;
See [[the full list of issues on GitHub>>https://github.com/phenotips/phenotips/issues?direction=asc&amp;milestone=9&amp;sort=created&amp;state=closed]].</content>
